nodes.bodyText:
But in order to change the bound of these generics, I need to move the parameter at the Loss class level instead of the call method level, otherwise the Java compiler does not allow me to override them. e.g.
public abstract class Loss<T, U> {
    public abstract Operand<T> call(Operand<U> labels, Operand<T> predictions, Operand<T> sampleWeights);
}

public final class Hinge extends Loss<TFloating, TIntegral> {
    @Override
    public Operand<T> call(Operand<U> labels, Operand<T> predictions, Operand<T> sampleWeights) {
    // ...
    }
}
Are we ok with this change or should we leave Loss parameter-less? ... or should we simply leave it as is (i.e. only bound to TNumber) and review this in a separate PR?

